        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Copake, or 12 miles southeast of Hudson, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Claverack, Livingston, Copake, Sheffield, Sharon, Norfolk, Ancram,
Philmont, Canaan, Millerton, Ashley Falls, Falls Village, Cornwall
Bridge, Claverack-Red Mills, Winsted, Salisbury, Hillsdale,
Colebrook, Cornwall, and Taghkanic.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
